ing `fails-java-run` routing from a real\n../4372-703e6b1e/docs/functional-spec.md:115:| `fails-java-run` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `javaTest` / JVM runtime stage. |\n../4372-703e6b1e/docs/functional-spec.md:119:| `fixes-java-run-fail` | PR | PR repairs a `fails-java-run` compatibility issue. |\n../4372-703e6b1e/docs/functional-spec.md:424:the stage-specific `fails-*` label — `fails-javac-compile`, `fails-java-run`,\n../7046-2e4f5133/forge/forge_metadata.py:163:LABEL_JAVA_RUN_FAIL = \"fails-java-run\"\n../7046-2e4f5133/forge/do_up_to_date_work.sh:90:      Process up to N fails-java-run tasks per run; 0 disables it. Defaults to\n../7046-2e4f5133/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:175:- `--label fails-java-run` invokes `fix_java_fails.py --java-run`.\n../7046-2e4f5133/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:176:- `fails-java-run` is included in the recognized pipeline label set and `--label` choices.\n../7046-2e4f5133/forge/docs/fix-java-run-fail.md:178:Successful `fails-java-run` issues finalize with `git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py`.\n../7046-2e4f5133/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:109:| `fails-java-run` | Issue | New-version compatibility failed during the `javaTest` / JVM runtime stage. |\n../7046-2e4f5133/docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:113:| `fixes-java-run-fail` | PR | PR repairs a `fails-java-run` compatibility issue. |\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/spec/fix-java-run-fail.md:174:- `--label fails-java-run` invokes `fix_java_fails.py --java-run`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/spec/fix-java-run-fail.md:175:- `fails-java-run` is included in the recognized pipeline label set and `--label` choices.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/spec/fix-java-run-fail.md:177:Successful `fails-java-run` issues finalize with `git_scripts/make_pr_java_run_fix.py`.\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/forge_metadata.py:106:LABEL_JAVA_RUN_FAIL = \"fails-java-run\"\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge1/metadata-forge/do-work.sh:46:      Process up to N fails-java-run tasks per run; 0 disables it. Defaults to\n/home/vjovanov/gdrive/sys/codex/history.jsonl:823:{\"session_id\":\"019de7ad-baf2-7522-a07a-cca2008ed2c5\",\"ts\":1777708570,\"text\":\"fails-java-run, fails-javac-compile, fails-native-image-build, fails-native-image-run, fixes-native-image-build-fail, GenAI, high-priority, human-intervention, human-intervention-fixed,\\n  library-add-new, library-unsupported-version, priority should be displayed in the spec\"}\n/home/vjovanov/gdrive/sys/codex/history.jsonl:1037:{\"session_id\":\"019decdf-d2e0-7f10-8f1a-d01345bddcd7\",\"ts\":1777796181,\"text\":\"No, Forge does not currently execute all tests locally that CI will execute.\\n\\n  The main gap is that Forge usually runs ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<single GAV> in three lanes from forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:168, then shared finalization from forge/utility_scripts/library_finalization.py:170. CI\\n  instead computes changed matrices from ci.json, pulls Docker images, disables Docker networking, validates metadata, and runs .github/workflows/scripts/run-consecutive-tests.sh:75 with GVM_TCK_LV for each tested-version batch.\\n\\n  Label Findings\\n\\n  library-new-request: partially covered locally. Missing CI-equivalent generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix, generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix, GVM_TCK_LV tested-version batches, Docker pre-pull/network-disable parity, validateIndexFiles, repo-wide\\n  validateLibraryStats, and checkDocLinks. Recent GenAI PR #5125 failing Validate index.json files is exactly this kind of gap.\\n\\n  library-update-request: same core gap as new-library work. Local generation/finalization is coordinate-scoped; CI validates changed metadata and newly added tested versions through matrix jobs from .github/workflows/test-changed-metadata.yml:45\\n  and .github/workflows/test-new-library-versions.yml:44.\\n\\n  fails-javac-compile / fixes-javac-fail: local repair can prove the selected coordinate compiles/tests, but does not prove every CI-tested version under the changed metadata/index diff.\\n\\n  fails-java-run / fixes-java-run-fail: same gap, and recent GenAI PR #5124 demonstrates it: Test changed metadata passed, but Test new library versions failed for org.scala-sbt:compiler-interface:1.10.0.\\n\\n  fails-native-image-run / fixes-native-image-run-fail: weakest local coverage. forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py:51 runs fixTestNativeImageRun, optionally one ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=<new>, then finalization. It does not use the shared three-lane\\n  _run_test_with_retry.\\n\\n  library-bulk-update: review-side only in Forge. It relies on CI completion rather than reproducing CI locally.\\n\\n  Review labels generally: Forge waits for completed CI before review via forge/forge_metadata.py:1114 and forge/forge_metadata.py:1312. That is a merge/review gate, not local CI-equivalent testing.\\n\\n  Recommended Fix\\n\\n  Add one reusable Forge verifier before PR creation that runs the same changed-matrix paths CI runs: generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix, generateChangedTestedVersionsMatrix, pullAllowedDockerImages, Docker networking disablement, checkMetadataFiles, run-\\n  consecutive-tests.sh, validateIndexFiles, validateLibraryStats, checkDocLinks, spotlessCheck, checkstyle, and Docker image scanning when relevant. That verifier should become the single gate for all PR-eligible Forge statuses. We also need to have a fixup step linked into the verification.\"}\n/home/vjovanov/gdrive/sys/codex/history.jsonl:1129:{\"session_id\":\"019ded91-ac83-71a3-87a1-b9a32f21bf5c\",\"ts\":1777807250,\"text\":\"[native-test-verify]     --module-path \\\\\\n[native-test-verify]     /home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm/ce/sdk/mxbuild/linux-amd64/GRAALVM_JAVA25/graalvm-25.1.0-dev+10.1/lib/svm/builder/reporter.jar:/home/vjovanov/c/graalvm-reachability-metadata/graalvm/ce/sdk/mxbuild/linux-amd64/GRAALVM_JAVA25/graalvm-25.1.0-dev+10.1/lib/svm/builder/espresso-svm.jar:/home/vjovanov